Wayne T. Smith










Wayne T. Smith








Member of the Board of Executive Directors of BASF SE







Curriculum Vitae

















Wayne T. Smith was born in Rochester, New York, United States, in 1960. From 1978 onwards, he studied Chemical Engineering at Syracuse University, United States, and received his bachelor’s degree in 1982. In 1989, he completed his master in Business Administration (MBA) at the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania, United States.












Professional Career











Close












 

2012
 
Member of the Board of Executive Directors of BASF SE, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of BASF Corporation (since May 2015), currently responsible for the divisions Catalysts, Coatings, Performance Materials, Market & Business Development, Site & Verbund Management North America, as well as Regional Functions & Country Platforms North America
2010
 
President, Polyurethanes division, Brussels, Belgium
2006
 
President, Catalysts division and Executive Vice President, BASF Corporation, Iselin and Florham Park, New Jersey, United States
2004
 
Group Vice President, Intermediates NAFTA, BASF Corporation, Florham Park, New Jersey, United States
2000
 
Vice President and General Manager, Specialty Construction Chemicals, W. R. Grace & Co., Cambridge, Massachusetts, United States
1998
 
Vice President and General Manager, Packaged Products, BOC Group, Murray Hill, New Jersey, United States
1997
 
Global Product Manager, Oxygen Packaged Products, BOC Group, Murray Hill, New Jersey, United States
1995
 
Regional Operations Manager, Northeastern Region, BOC Group, Murray Hill, New Jersey, United States
1993
 
Business Manager, Oxygen On-Site Plants, BOC Group, Murray Hill, New Jersey, United States
1989
 
Manager Finance and Planning, Sales Manager Process Systems, BOC Group, Murray Hill, New Jersey, United States




















