 Executive Profiles   
Wayne T. Smith










Wayne T. Smith



















Wayne T. Smith is Chairman and CEO of BASF in North America; a role he assumed on May 1, 2015.
A member of the BASF SE Board of Executive Directors since 2012, Wayne leads all activities within BASF’s North American business region and also bears responsibility for the company’s global Catalysts, Coatings and Performance Materials business divisions.
Prior to his current role, Wayne served as President of BASF’s global Polyurethanes Division, headquartered in Brussels, Belgium. A 26-year veteran of the chemical industry, Wayne joined BASF in 2004 as Group Vice President of the North American Intermediates regional business unit.
Before joining BASF, Wayne held the position of Vice President and General Manager Specialty Construction Chemicals, W.R. Grace & Co., Cambridge, MA.  Previous to that role, Wayne had served in various financial, operations, business management and executive capacities with BOC Group, Murray Hill, NJ.
Born in Rochester, New York, Wayne holds a Bachelor of Science in Chemical Engineering from Syracuse University and a Master of Business Administration (MBA) from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.

















